==English==
===Interjection===
''slang''. the shouting of "chi-hike" as a salute; hence, a noisy demonstration. In Australia and (less commonly) New Zealand, jeering, [[banter]], [[cheek]]
==Reference==
John A. Simpson and Edmund S.C. Weiner, eds. "chi-hike", ''The Oxford English Dictionary,'' 2nd ed. (1989)